external_knowledge:
- "compass that guides the investor's treasure" refers to the portfolio_name and stock_name, which serve as a guide for the investor's investments;
- "average daily fluctuations" refers to the average daily return, calculated as AVG((sp.close_price - sp.open_price) / sp.open_price) * 100;
- "overall treasure growth" refers to the total return, calculated as (MAX(sp.close_price) - MIN(sp.open_price)) / MIN(sp.open_price) * 100;
- "treasure map" refers to the portfolio_name;
- "precious stone" refers to the stock_name;
- "treasure hunter with the map number 1" refers to the user with user_id = 1;
- "navigation records" refers to the stock price data, with at least 30 days of data required.
